AIM: Creation of a redis having a master and 3 replica sets having a customize bitnami/redis image which has pushed to artifact registry on GCP

Description: This configuration has been created due to bitnami has stopped giving support to their docker.io bitnami registry from august 28, 2025.
All existing container images have been migrated from the public catalog (docker.io/bitnami) to the “Bitnami Legacy” repository (docker.io/bitnamilegacy), where they will no longer receive updates.

# Lets keep a copy of redis image into your own artifact registry of your gcp account.

Step 1:
create a Dockerfile and build the image with the following code:

FROM bitnamilegacy/redis:latest

Step 2:
# build the docker image with appropriate tag based on your gcp account artifact registry. In my case directory has been set up with asia-south1 region

docker build -t asia-south1-docker.pkg.dev/<repo>/<directory> .

docker push asia-south1-docker.pkg.dev/<repo>/<directory>:latest

Step 3:

# now take that image and create a values.yaml file to install through helm chart


