1. "commonConfiguration" has been set up here, that means whenever storage goes beyond 3Gi, least used keys will get deleted automatically.
2. You can give toleration and nodeSelector based on your nodepool set up.
3. Bitnami doesn't let you install insecure images. You need to change allowInsecureImages to false.

Command:
helm install <your release name> bitnamilegacy/redis -f value.yaml -n <namespace> --set global.security.allowInsecureImages=true